y AFB]])\n: [[254th Combat Communications Group]], [[Grand Prairie Armed Forces Reserve Complex|Grand Prairie AFRC]]\n: Band of the Southwest, 531st Air Force Band, [[NAS JRB Fort Worth]] \n: [[Texas Air National Guard|Headquarters, Texas Air National Guard]], [[Camp Mabry]], Austin\n*'''[[Utah Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[151st Air Refueling Wing]], [[Salt Lake City International Airport|Roland R. Wright ANGB]]\n*'''[[Vermont Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[158th Fighter Wing]], [[Burlington Air National Guard Base|Burlington ANGB]] (former Ethan Allen AFB)\n*'''[[Virginia Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[192d Fighter Wing]], [[Langley AFB]]\n*'''[[Washington Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[141st Air Refueling Wing]], [[Fairchild AFB]]\n: [[194th Regional Support Wing]], [[Joint Base Lewis-McChord]] (aka [[McChord AFB]])\n: Air Force Band of the Northwest, 560th Air Force Band, [[Fairchild AFB]]\n*'''[[West Virginia Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[130th Airlift Wing]], [[Charleston Air National Guard Base|Charleston ANGB]]\n: [[167th Airlift Wing]], [[Shepherd Field Air National Guard Base|Shepherd Field ANGB]]\n*'''[[Wisconsin Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[115th Fighter Wing]], [[Truax Field Air National Guard Base|Truax Field ANGB]]\n: [[128th Air Refueling Wing]], [[General Mitchell Air National Guard Base|General Mitchell ANGB]]\n: [[Volk Field Combat Readiness Training Center]], [[Volk Field Air National Guard Base|Volk Field ANGB]]\n*'''[[Wyoming Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[153d Airlift Wing]], [[Cheyenne Regional Airport|Cheyenne ANGB]]\n: Camp Guernsey Joint Training Center, Guernsey\n{{Col-end}}\n\n===Federal District and Territories===\n{{Col-start}}\n{{Col-break}}\n* '''[[District of Columbia Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[113th Wing]], [[Joint Base Andrews]] (former [[Andrews AFB]]), [[Maryland]]\n* '''[[Guam Air National Guard]]'''\n: 254th Air Base Group, [[Andersen AFB]], [[Joint Region Marianas]]\n{{Col-break}}\n* '''[[Puerto Rico Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[156th Airlift Wing]], [[Mu\u00f1iz Air National Guard Base|Muniz ANGB]]\n: [[141st Air Control Squadron]], [[Rafael Hern\u00e1ndez Airport]] (former [[Ramey AFB]])\n* '''[[Virgin Islands Air National Guard]]'''\n: [[285th Civil Engineering Squadron]], [[St. Croix]] ANGS\n{{Col-end}}\n\n==List of Air National Guard Leaders==\nThis is a list of the senior leaders or Generals of the Air National Guard. The title has changed over time: The Assistant Chief, National Guard Bureau for Air,; Chief, Air Force Division, National Guard Bureau; Director Air National Guard.<ref>\n  {{Citation\n |title=Major General Winston P. Wilson Bio \n |url=http://www.af.mil/information/bios/bio.asp?bioid=7623 \n |accessdate=24 December 2011 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20121213001604/http://www.af.mil/information/bios/bio.asp?bioid=7623 \n |archivedate=13 December 2012 \n  \n}}\n</ref><ref>\n  {{Citation\n  |title = Active Major Command and ANG Leaders\n  |publisher = Air Force Association\n  |date=May 2011\n  |magazine = Air Force Magazine\n  |page = 106\n  |url = http://www.airforce-magazine.com/MagazineArchive/Magazine%20Documents/2011/May%202011/0511leaders.pdf\n  |accessdate =20 December 2011\n }}\n</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Number !! Name !! From !! To\n|-\n|1 || [[Colonel (United States)|Col]] [[William A. R. Robertson]] || 28 November 1945 || October 1948\n|-\n|2 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[George G. Finch]] || October 1948 || 25 September 1950\n|-\n|3 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[Earl T. Ricks]] || 13 October 1950 || 4 January 1954\n|-\n|4 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[Winston P. Wilson]] || 26 January 1954 || 5 August 1962\n|-\n|5 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[I. G. Brown]] || 6 August 1962 || 19 April 1974\n|-\n|6 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[John J. Pesch]] || 20 April 1974 || 31 January 1977\n|-\n|7 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[John T. Guice]] || 1 February 1977 || 1 April 1981\n|-\n|8 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[John B. Conaway]] || 1 April 1981 || 1 November 1988\n|-\n|9 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[Philip G. Killey]] || 1 November 1988 || 28 January 1994\n|-\n|10 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[Donald W. Shepperd]] || 28 January 1994 || 28 January 1998\n|-\n|11 || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[Paul A. Weaver|Paul A. Weaver Jr.]] || 28 January 1998 || 3 December 2001\n|-\n|(Acting) || [[Brigadier general (United States)|Brig Gen]] David A. Brubaker || 3 December 2001 || 3 June 2002\n|-\n|12 || [[Lieutenant General (United States)|Lt Gen]] [[Daniel James III]] || 3 June 2002 || 20 May 2006\n|-\n|13 || [[Lieutenant General (United States)|Lt Gen]] [[Craig R. McKinley]] || 20 May 2006 || 17 November 2008\n|-\n|(Acting) || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] [[Emmett R. Titshaw Jr.]] || 17 November 2008 || 2 February 2009\n|-\n|14 || [[Lieutenant General (United States)|Lt Gen]] [[Harry M. Wyatt III]] || 2 February 2009 || 30 January 2013\n|-\n|15 || [[Lieutenant General (United States)|Lt Gen]] [[Stanley E. Clarke III]] || 22 March 2013 || 18 December 2015\n|-\n|(Acting) || [[Major General (United States)|Maj Gen]] Brian G. Neal || 18 December 2015 || 10 May 2016\n|-\n|16 || [[Lieutenant General (United States)|Lt Gen]] [[L. Scott Rice]] || 10 May 2016 ||        ||        \n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|World War I|World War II}}\n*[[Space National Guard]]\n*[[Air National Guard Readiness Center]]\n*[[I.G. Brown Air National Guard Training and Education Center]]\n*[[Flying Squadrons of the Air National Guard]]\n'''Comparable organizations'''\n*[[Army National Guard]] (U.S. Army)\n*[[United States Army Reserve]]\n*[[United States Marine Corps Reserve]]\n*[[United States Navy Reserve]]\n*[[United States Coast Guard Reserve]]\n*[[Air Force Reserve Command]] (U.S. Air Force)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Sources==\n*{{Air Fo